{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require Local Authorities to let motorists pay local road charges before fines",
        "additional_details": "Too many times people contravene local road traffic charging schemes without realising by inadvertently driving in areas unknown to them and receiving a fine ranging from \u00a360.00 to \u00a3200.00. A letter should be sent instead of a PCN stating that they have contravened a local charging scheme and are given a period of time to pay the original charge plus any postage or admin costs",
        "background": "Local Authorities should be required to send a warning letter to motorists if they have contravened a local road charging scheme, giving them the chance to pay the road charge first, before imposing a more expensive fine. ",
